title: rclone v1.38 "panic: runtime error: index out of range" when listing an S3 bucket
body:
> What is your rclone version (eg output from `rclone -V`)

```
2017/12/18 15:32:30 DEBUG : Using config file from "/Users/jamshid/.rclone.conf"
2017/12/18 15:32:30 DEBUG : rclone: Version "v1.38" starting with parameters ["rclone" "-vv" "--dump-headers" "ls" "jam:problematic"]
```

> Which OS you are using and how many bits (eg Windows 7, 64 bit)

macOS High Sierra 10.13.2 (17C88)

> Which cloud storage system are you using? (eg Google Drive)

S3-compatible system (Caringo Swarm)

> The command you were trying to run (eg `rclone copy /tmp remote:tmp`)

```
rclone -vv --dump-headers ls jam:problematic
```
